data.description: Welcome home! Stunning and well updated 4 bedroom, 3 full bath, 2624 sqft, "Dorchester" model single family home located in the highly sought after Maryland City community! Features of this fantastic home include: a long concrete driveway with side entry, vinyl siding/recent windows, HVAC and roof both replaced within the last 7 years, and new carpet. Upon entry you have the large and open living room area with main window for lots of light, complete with a beautiful wood burning stove accented with a tile hearth to help warm those cold winter nights. Continuing towards the back of the home we have the fully updated kitchen complete with long granite counter tops, lots of updated wood cabinetry, all stainless appliances (electric stove, refrigerator, dishwasher, microwave), pantry, a gorgeous ceramic tile floor, and the adjacent dining area accented with custom built cabinetry for those special gatherings. Walking down the hall to the left we have the well updated guest full bath with a ceramic tile floor and surround. As we continue towards the back of the home, we have two very spacious secondary bedrooms with new carpet and tons of closet space that's perfect for guests or family. Continuing back the other way we have the ginormous "owners" bedroom suite with a large master "walk-in" closet, and a fully remodeled/large and private master bath with a decorative ceramic tile floor and surround. Moving downstairs to the fully finished lower level you will be greeted by a large and open recreation area with recessed lighting that's perfect for entertaining on those lazy football Sunday's, an adjacent and very large 4th bedroom, a custom full bath with ceramic tile/surround, and towards the back of the home in the storage/laundry area there is an easy access walk-out/walk-up stairwell. Last but not least, a quick trip through the kitchen and out the rear sliders leads us to a very large and beautiful fenced back yard (with shed) that's perfect for those upcoming summer bar-b-ques! Lions, and tigers, and bears...oh my! Adjacent to shopping/dining and minutes from NSA/Ft. Meade, MARC, Baltimore, and DC!
